subject: w01hwtwqdop
comments: In line with psychological principles like risk aversion, I typically preferred to take the safe option when both outcomes saw a decrease in objects, while usually taking the risky one when both outcomes saw an increase in objects. This is because when I was posed with a positive situation such as taking objects away from the screen, I wanted a positive outcome, no matter the extent. On the other hand, when I was posed with a negative situation, I wanted to try and avoid a negative outcome altogether, even if the risk of eliminating such an outcome could lead to an even more negative outcome.
